            I'm a registered architect, LEED Accredited Professional, and
            <a href="https://ltu.edu/faculty/neiswender-aia-kurt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Assistant Professor of Practice</a> at
            <strong>Lawrence Technological University</strong> in the College of
            Architecture and Design. I'm also the founder and principal architect at
            <a href="https://www.urbancolab.design" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Urban Colab Architecture, L3C</a>
            in Flint, Michigan.
          </p>

          <p>
            With 20+ years of professional experience&mdash;from firms in Los Angeles
            and Connecticut to my own community-driven practice in Flint&mdash;my work
            sits at the intersection of architectural practice, education, and
            computation. I lead community-driven projects in sustainable housing and
            adaptive reuse, including Gray Street Apartments, Orchard Grove and Manor,
            and the Avalon Village Community Kitchen.
          </p>

          <h2>Teaching</h2>

          <p>
            My teaching centers on <strong>comprehensive design</strong>&mdash;the
            integration of building systems, environmental performance, and design
            intent. I teach HVAC and Water Systems, Acoustics and Illumination, and
            the Comprehensive Design Studio at both undergraduate and graduate levels.
            I'm interested in how computational tools can make architects more fluent
            in the technical dimensions of their work without losing the poetry.
          </p>

          <h2>Philosophy</h2>

          <p>
            I believe in <strong>learning in public</strong>. The digital garden on
            this site is where I think out loud&mdash;sharing rough ideas alongside
            polished ones. Architecture is a discipline that benefits from open
            discourse, and the best way to learn is to teach.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also co-host the
            <a href="https://www.coffeesketchpodcast.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Coffee Sketch Podcast</a>
            with Jamie Crawley, AIA&mdash;a global design podcast with 190+ episodes
            and listeners in 80+ countries, exploring architecture, creativity, and
            technology through the medium of the sketch.
          </p>

